default.1
default              
defaultHigh Speed 1 (HS1), formerly known as the Channel Tunnel Rail Link, is a 109 kilometre high speed rail line which connects London and the Channel Tunnel, passing through Kent.  HS1 is operated by HS1 Ltd under a 30 year Concession Agreement with the 
defaultSoS
default for Transport. HS1 is Britain's first high speed railway and the UK leg of the Paris-Brussels
default-Köln-Amsterdam-London (PBKAL) TEN-T priority project. The line successfully carries international and domestic passenger high speed services 
defaultand
default freight services. 
defaultHS1 has delivered significant time-savings for Kent commuters and international travellers. Performance is currently at world-class levels.
default&#xa0;
default2.2
default              
defaultHS1 Ltd is regulated through a framework of primary and secondary legislation enacted by the UK Government. The regulatory framework has been established to recognise the unique characteristics of HS1 while seeking to ensure that, as much as possible, HS1 Ltd is subject to similar regulatory supervision to the classic 
defaultUK 
defaultrail network.
